This paper discusses honeypots, which are used in computer security to detect and analyze attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, honeypots are often used in network security, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses methodologies for analyzing honeypot data, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper may also touch on data analysis techniques, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
